Subject: [PATCH 029/194] HACK series: for working qdsp6
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Unfortunately, there are multiple slightly different versions used across various forks, we’ve never really converged on a single one.

Mainline: doesn’t make sense in the current state. The current design with the q6voiced service required in userspace has too many integration issues, it conflicts with all other ongoing efforts to improve call audio support in standard userspace components like PipeWire. This is partly also why call audio tends to be unreliable.

Signed-off-by: David Heidelberg <david@ixit.cz>

